The paper deals with graph-based data analysis and specifically focuses on the problem of finding clusters of well-connected nodes in a graph. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper proposes new techniques for automatically learning how to set clustering resolution parameters, which involves optimization and machine learning techniques. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Systems and Control (cs.SD), and Data Mining (cs.DM).
